      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WINSOME JOSIE (3) has a strong record this trip with six wins and six placings from 14 starts. Comes off a (22.73) win last time, scoring by 4.5 lengths in a Grade 5 over 401m at this track. Looks suited here and rates on top. MISTER ANATOLY (8) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Grade 5 winner three back (22.96) at this track over 401m. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. TOWERING LUKE (4) struggled in tougher grade last start after settling well back at Bulli, but prior to that won by half a length at Bulli (19.27) beating Forty's Boy in a Grade 5 on April 28. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from three starts. Should be about the mark. TAKE HIS EYES (2) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to turn the form around.",
